    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="1406"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1406">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/666.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Vice Consul <persName type="to">Davis</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 204.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 21, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has received your despatch No. 557
                    of May 8, 1915, in regard to the demand by the Constitutionalist faction for the
                    re-payment to them of all taxes paid to the Convencionistas during the latter’s
                    occupation.</p>
                <p>Your attention is called to the Department’s telegram of May 28, 1915, informing
                    you that it had issued appropriate instructions in the matter to Mr. John K.
                    Silliman, American Consul, who is now at Vera Cruz.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Acting Secretary of State: <lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilbur J. Carr.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
